---
title: Moo Shu Pork Bowls with Cabbage, Scallions & Buttery Rice
description: This saucy, sweet, and spicy dish is ready in just 15 minutes—that’s faster than it takes to order delivery! Ground pork is browned with cabbage and scallions, then simmered in a blend of sweet Thai chili sauce, soy glaze, hoisin, and lime juice. It’s all spooned over buttery rice and garnished with sesame seeds for a nutty crunch.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/moo-shu-pork-bowls-05b96033.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/moo-shu-pork-bowls-61cb2d5696416a73f4200714-0dc23866.pdf
time required: 20 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/moo-shu-pork-bowls-61cb2d5696416a73f4200714
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 790 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 89 g
  sugar: 39 g
  protein: 26 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1450 mg
cuisine: Asian
---

Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Quarter @Lime{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Ground Pork{10%oz} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Stir scallion whites and @Shredded Red Cabbage{4%oz} into pan with pork; cook, stirring occasionally, until just tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @Hoisin Sauce{2%tbsp}, @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{1%oz}, 2 1/2 tbsp @Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tbsp}, and @Sugar{1/2%tsp} until thoroughly combined. Turn off heat.

Taste and season with juice from half the lime, @salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Fluff rice with a fork and stir in @Butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls and top with moo shu pork. Sprinkle with scallion greens and as many @Sesame Seeds{1%tbsp} as you like. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.